{"ts":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z","author":"codex-root","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-bnmlsc"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Sentry PM-CLI-2G: make merge-driver installation permission failures actionable"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Sentry reports a handled high-severity production failure when pm merge install attempts to configure the repository-local merge driver in a workspace where .git/config cannot be locked. Harden the merge-install boundary so expected read-only or permission-constrained repositories return a deterministic, actionable pm error instead of surfacing a raw child-process failure, while preserving normal field-aware merge-driver installation."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":1},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":[]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"codex-root"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-92if"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/severity","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/environment","value":"production CI and permission-constrained Git workspaces"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/repro_steps","value":"Run pm merge install in a valid Git worktree where repository-local Git configuration cannot be written."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/expected_result","value":"The command fails with a stable pm error code and remediation guidance, classifies the expected permission constraint appropriately in telemetry, and leaves Git configuration unchanged."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/actual_result","value":"The underlying git config command fails with 'could not lock config file .git/config: Permission denied' and produces handled high-severity Sentry issue PM-CLI-2G."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/affected_version","value":"2026.7.21"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/component","value":"merge-install"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/customer_impact","value":"Agents in read-only CI or sandboxed worktrees receive a raw infrastructure error and observability records an expected environmental constraint as a high-severity product failure."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-g5sx","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"},{"id":"pm-i4fx","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"},{"id":"pm-iwsj","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"},{"id":"pm-wc1r","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z"}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for PM-CLI-2G, merge.pm-item-toon, git config, merge install, and permission denied; no item tracked this exact failure. Live Sentry evidence: PM-CLI-2G is new, unresolved, handled, count 2, first seen 2026-07-21T21:37:22.513Z and last seen 2026-07-21T21:37:23.120Z in @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.21. Permalink: https://unbrained.sentry.io/issues/135741631/."}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Acceptance scope: cover a real temporary Git repository with a deliberately non-writable repository config boundary; assert deterministic error metadata and remediation text; prove no partial merge-driver configuration; preserve successful installation and idempotency; verify telemetry/Sentry classification for expected permission constraints; update merge-safety documentation."}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Permission-constrained Git metadata is a normal execution environment for CI and review sandboxes. Merge-driver setup should distinguish an expected environmental inability to mutate local Git config from an unexpected application defect."}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"192b9d3b824929349d44c9700c69c315ecd9a604b826c1b03e992e5e80cb2a19","message":""}
